<title>AUSTRALIA: RTRS-Discovery bid unconditional - Premier.</title>
<headline>RTRS-Discovery bid unconditional - Premier.</headline>
<dateline>SYDNEY 1996-12-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>Premier Oil Australia Pty Ltd, a subdidiary of Britain's Premier Oil Plc, said its 81 cent per share bid for Discovery Petroleum Ltd has been extended to December 23 and has been declared unconditional.</p>
<p>&quot;The conditions waived were 50.1 percent minimum acceptance and there being no prescribed conditions,&quot; Premier said.  </p>
<p>Premier said it was also arranging for shareholders to be paid on an accelerated basis of five days after acceptance.</p>
<p>Last week Oil Search Ltd said it would accept Premier Oil's 81 cent per share bid for its 10.1 percent stake in Discovery.</p>
<p>Premier earlier increased its bid to 81 cents from 80 cents and Discovery's directors recommended shareholders accept the offer.</p>
<p>-- Sydney Newsroom 61-2 373-1800</p>
